items.name: RoXL
items.description:
RoXL is the SDXL evolution of my Rendered model, though with a lot more data and variety thrown in. I've mainly focused on characters, but there's enough variety of other things in the dataset to keep it fairly flexible. Fine tuned off of Yamer's UnstableDiffusers V5.

My main focuses, and (hopefully) the strengths of the model are:

  • Distinctive style

  • Expressive and natural feeling faces

  • Variety in face shapes and types. Avoiding every generation looking like the same person.

  • Ability to get varied and natural poses

  • A variety of scifi and fantasy themes and keywords. (good elf ears, scifi outfits, etc.)

  • Extra flexibility and variety in ethnicities

  • Extra control over hair, bodytypes, etc, though base SDXL is much better than 1.5 in this respect.

Recommended (tested) Settings:

  • Euler A(ncestral) Sampler, 30 steps, gives a very painterly feel

  • DPM++ 2M Karras, 30 steps, 8.0 CFG, (Courtesy of Hailoknight) gives details and coherence I didn't know was possible

  • further testing of varied settings to come soon, it seems to work great with a wide variety.

This is the 1.0 release of the model, so still slightly rough around the edges, but still extremely usable and capable of amazing things.

Finally, Training SDXL models gets pricy. If you want to help me continue experimenting and improving models, please consider tossing me a few dollars on ko-fi.

items.name: Fooocus - Diva Styles Expansion
items.description:
This Styles Expansion for Fooocus adds over 70 new style prompts to the Fooocus Style menu.

To use this expansion you'll need to install Fooocus: https://github.com/lllyasviel/Fooocus.git

(EDIT 08-26-2023: As of today my styles have been merged with the official download of Fooocus - so if you have a new install of Fooocus there is no need to download my styles expansion as this expansion is now included with the official download of Fooocus. Those who have a version that's older or hasn't been updated may still want to download this expansion. You can now find my styles in the Styles menu starting from "cinematic-diva" to "Whimsical and Playful".)

I added over 70 visual styles and art styles. It took some research on the different art styles to know how to prompt for each style and I learned a lot. They're not perfect, as many styles are new to me and I had to make educated guesses based on the style's descriptions on how to build the prompt scripts for them. So they might not be 100% true to the styles, but they do add a nice amount of artistic variety!

This expansion and it's 70+ visual styles took a few hours to compile and create, so if you have a minute please leave a rating for this. I'd very much appreciate it! :)

If you enjoy this or get some creative fun out of it please consider buying me a coffee: https://ko-fi.com/3diva It really helps me to keep creating new content for you guys! :)

~ Diva

items.name: ezpz22step1080p
items.description:
needed

https://civitai.com/models/24690/comfyui-facerestore-node

recommended

https://civitai.com/models/71980/comfyui-manager

This workflow works for 1.5, 2, XL. Ensure you select the proper VAE for the Checkpoints loaded. I don't use 1.5 any more, so there may be issues with it. When using 1.5 ensure to lower the CFG's to about 4-7, it's not as good at reading.

You can actually mix and match 1.5 and XL, or mix 2 xl models, or 2 1.5 models. The Upscale fix has its own checkpoint, vae, lora and prompts

This workflow is used mostly for 16:9 but can do any resolution with the custom latent, just make sure you set all upscale resolutions properly.

Default 16:9 resolution latents are in the settings area, you need to drag the pink latent circle to the base image ksampler.

Fast upscale is enabled automatically, it's not great, but sometimes works well with high quality bases and is very fast, turn on and off the upscalers in the settings bottom right. You need to have inline upscaling on, the rest help with quality but are slower.

If you want to use a model upscale, remove the bypass on the "model upscale" at the bottom of the settings

Recommendations - use the lowest x model that looks good, they progressively get better quality, but much slower, just inline can work but iffy./

If upscaling to 4k is not great, add 2-4 steps to the finishing step and use model upscaling. I also change the inline upscale to 1440p (Slower)

2x_NMKD-UpgifLiteV2_210k

4x_NMKD-UpgifLiteV2_210k

4x_NMKD-Siax_200k

4x UtraSharp

8x NMKD-Superscale_150000_G

I use 4x_NMKD-UpgifLiteV2 for the first upscale and a 4x ultrasharp for the 4k upscale, I start 1280x720 mostly.

Face restore is tricky and is needed the lower res you start with. Included are 2 points of restore that are default disabled.

1st restore point is after the inline upscale, it has less impact on the final result but can help if you're upscaling from lower res.

2nd restore is after the samplers are done and has a big impact on the look of the person,

With 1280x720 and higher, face restore is not really needed anymore with decent checkpoints

XL Checkpoints tested on RealitiesEdgeXL, atxl, copaxmelodiesxl, crystalclearxl, dynavisionxlAllinone, fudukiMix, morphxl, realcartoonxl, rhapsodyxl, sdvn6realxl, xlyamersrealistic -- 1.5 Checkpoints tested on Kmain, realmoon

items.name: Karen Gillan - SDXL
items.description:
Karen Sheila Gillan (/ˈɡɪlən/; born 28 November 1987) is a Scottish actress and filmmaker. She gained recognition for her work in British film and television, particularly for playing Amy Pond, a primary companion to the Eleventh Doctor in the science fiction series Doctor Who (2010–2013), for which she received several awards and nominations. Her early film roles include Ally in the thriller film Outcast (2010) and Jane Lockhart in the romantic comedy film Not Another Happy Ending (2013). She also worked on the stage while in Britain, appearing in John Osborne's play Inadmissible Evidence (2011).

Gillan made her transition to Hollywood starring as Kaylie Russell in the horror film Oculus (2013), her first commercial success in the United States, and thereafter played the lead in the ABC sitcom Selfie (2014). She achieved international stardom for portraying Nebula in the Marvel Cinematic Universe superhero films Guardians of the Galaxy (2014), Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 (2017), Avengers: Infinity War (2018), Avengers: Endgame (2019), Thor: Love and Thunder (2022), and Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 3 (2023). She additionally was praised for her portrayals of Ruby Roundhouse in the action films Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle (2017) and Jumanji: The Next Level (2019), Sam in the comedy film Gunpowder Milkshake (2021) and her double role in the sci-fi thriller film Dual (2022).

No refiner used on the photos. All raw output without face restoration or other tricks

Rather than using AnythingV5 like normal, I used Hassaku. Though, unfortunately, I can't really seem to know the specifics such as steps, weights, clip skips, epochs, etc., it's the one downside I have to say with using PixAI to generate LoRAs compared to how I prefer making LoRAs.

Still, I like how it produced the Nurse, but I will be doing the Nurse LoRA the old fashioned way (I have the model produced, just need to test and produce the images)
